        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 23 at 7:08PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 708 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Brighton, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

This strong thunderstorm will be near...
South Lyon around 715 PM EDT.
Novi around 720 PM EDT.

Other locations impacted by this storm include Lakeland, Orchard
Lake, Island Lake State Recreation Area, Chilson, Commerce, Wolverine
Lake, New Hudson, Farmington, Walled Lake, and Wixom.

People attending Brighton Street Art Fair , and Novi Taco Fest and
Art  should seek safe shelter immediately!
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
